title: Top Menu Components
content:
The Top Menu comprises of:
Logout
Site Map
Desktop
Links
My Favorites
Applications
FYear
Entity

title: Logout Functionality
content: You can logout by this logout icon to enable system register time out.

title: Site Map Functionality
content: You can view the whole process in outline form using the Site Map.

title: Desktop Functionality
content: You can navigate the system to go back to its main page/desktop mode using Desktop.

title: Links Functionality
content: Links shows a list of quick links to the individual Applications in Globe3, grouped by functional areas.

title: My Favorites Functionality
content: This area allows the user to set personal shortcuts to any section of Globe3. To add a new Favorite, click on Organize Favorites. On the entry screen, check the Add box and assign a Favorite Name to it. After submitting the entry, the Favorites will be shown in the My Favorites list.

title: Add a new Favorite
content:
Click on Organize Favorites.
On the entry screen, check the Add box.
Assign a Favorite Name to it.
Submit the entry. The Favorites will be shown in the My Favorites list.

title: Applications Select Box Functionality
content: To scroll from application to application, use this select box. The sub-folders will show list of modules which you can access. Select the item and left-click.

title: FYear Select Box Functionality
content: Real-time access to different financial year's reports and records can be accessed via this financial year select box. Administrators can set the default financial year when new financial year is opened. This select box enables toggle from one financial to another. The selected financial or active financial year is shown in the top right section of the screen. Data entry for transactions and the running of key financial reports can be made for each financial year by toggling to the required year.

title: Entity Select Box Functionality
content: Globe3 is a multi-company system. Once more than one company has been set up, this select box will show all the companies listing. Click and select the company required to access into the company's records. This company listing can be controlled through user access privilege. See "User Management". The selected active company is shown in the center top section of the screen.

title: Languages Select Box Functionality
content:
Globe3 has optional simultaneous multi-lingual module. Different language interface can be accessed through this select box. The available languages are English, Chinese Simplified, Chinese Traditional, Japanese, Korean, Vietnamese, Thai, and Malay, Indonesian.
For example, by clicking on Chinese Simplified, the entire screen will be translated to a Chinese language interface.

title: Transaction / Forms Navigation Links
content:
The main navigation location for each transaction section is near the top right portion of the screen. For most transactions you will see the following links:
Prelim - To show prelim page
New - To enter new records
List - To list all or most recent records, depending on system setting
Report - To create specific transactional reports
Admin - To set up auto num, taps, lock/unlock doc
Print - To print document per date range
Search - Advance search function for the particular sub-module

title: Viewing Recent Records in Bank Payment
content: When you click on "List" (e.g., in Bank Payment), you will see a listing of recent records. This example shows Bank Payment records for FY2010 with columns for Amount, Date, Docm No., Ref Num, Cheq No., Name, Draft (13), Posted Final (206), along with details like General Ledger and 182,032.00 SGD.

title: Interpreting Icons in Record Listings
content:
The first column, with the bin icon, is for deleting the record. If the checkbox is not showing, it means the record cannot be deleted for control purpose.
The second column, with the pencil icon, is for links to edit the document. If the mouse cursor changes to a Hand shape icon when it is over the link, it means the link is available for editing; otherwise, it means the record is not editable.
The third column with the telescope icon is for viewing the record entry.
The icon with the Gear image is for document history tracking.
The icon with the magnifying glass beside Name is for print form preview.
The last column represents links, from left to right respectively, for:
Attach document to record
Clone record
Void record
GL double entries view
Workflow status
Multiple print view
Edit document number

title: Master Users Management Overview
content:
Path: Globe3 Central > Master Control > Master Settings > Master Users Mgmt
Master-level users can be added by master administrators. These users get access to all or some companies based on assigned privileges.
Names can be selected from existing holding, group, or subsidiary companies.
A user privilege access matrix is available to guide administrators.
If the user is from the Employees module of the Human Resource application, they must be created in the group/parent company, specifying their subsidiary.
If the user is not in the Employee database, check the checkbox to bypass staff name selection.

title: Setting Employee Sales/Purchase Executive Category
content:
Click on the Categories tab.
Check the relevant department (e.g., Sales or Purchase) to specify the employee as a sales or purchase executive.

title: Creating a User from Template or Scratch
content:
User can be created from a template or from scratch.
If from a template, select the applicable template name and the 'Default Settings' section can be left blank.
If created anew, check the 'Selected' box for Applications the user will have access to, and specify whether such access is view only or full access.

title: Assigning User Details and Privileges
content:
Assign the new user's User Type, System Role, Company and Login ID, Password and Validity Period.
Fine-tune the access privilege of new user down to the specific companies and functions.
To save these settings for future use, check the box for "Save as User Access Template" and assign a name to it. These same settings can then be applied to any new users created later on.

title: Creating Users using a Template
content:
If other users have similar access rights, use a saved template.
From the "New" page, select the applicable User Access Template.
Click on Next.
Change the details as required. (Note: multiple templates can be saved, e.g., for Accounts, Purchasing, Sales).
